00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:17,300
to extract Yo-Yo's data

223
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:20,300
and bring it out into computational environments

224
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:23,420
what is the computational capacity of a musical instrument?

225
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,740
As we continue on this tangent

226
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:26,180
and we'll share a return to CBA.

227
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:31,180
Yeah, so one part of that is to understand the computing

228
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:36,100
and if you look at like the finest timescale

229
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,540
and length scale you need to model the physics,

230
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:39,980
it's not heroic.

231
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:42,900
A good GPU can do teraflops today.

232
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:45,020
That used to be a national class supercomputer,

233
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,300
now it's just a GPU.

234
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,940
And that's about if you take the timescales

235
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,700
and length scales relevant for the physics,

236
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:53,380
that's about the scale of the physics computing.

237
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,780
For Yo-Yo, what was really driving it

238
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:59,500
was he's completely unsentimental about the Strad.

239
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:02,180
It's not that it makes some magical wiggles

240
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:03,380
in the sound wave,

241
00:11:03,380 --> 00:11:05,940
it's performance as a controller,

242
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:09,860
how he can manipulate it as an interface device.

243
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:11,500
Interface between one and what exactly?

244
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,820
Him and sound.

245
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:13,660
Okay, him and sound.

246
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:15,700
And so what it led to was,

